@page "/components/breadcrumbs"

<PageTitle>Breadcrumbs - Tavenem Blazor Framework</PageTitle>

<Heading Level="HeadingLevel.H1">Breadcrumbs</Heading>

<p>
    The breadcrumbs component displays a simple inline list with separators between each item. It is
    intended for showing the navigational hierarchy of the current page. Usually the elements are
    links to to the app areas which conceptually contain the current view.
</p>

<p>
    To create a breadcrumb list, add the <code>breadcrumbs</code> class to an element (usually an
    <code>ol</code> or other list).
</p>

<p>
    If you set the <code>aria-current</code> attribute to <code>true</code> on any element in the
    list, its appearance will change to visually indicate that there is no need to interact with it.
    Links can be fully disabled, if necessary, by removing the <code>href</code> attribute, or using
    an <a href="./components/anchor-link">AnchorLink</a> component with the <code>Disabled</code>
    parameter set to <code>true</code>.
</p>

<CodeExample Code="@(@"<nav aria-label=""breadcrumb"">
    <ol class=""breadcrumbs"">
        <li><a href=""./"">Home</a></li>
        <li>Components</li>
        <li aria-current=""page""><a href=""./components/breadcrumbs"">Breadcrumbs</a></li>
    </ol>
</nav>")" />

<Heading Level="HeadingLevel.H2">Customization</Heading>

<p>
    The separator between items can be customized by setting the
    <code>--tavenem-breadcrumb-divider</code> CSS property, either on the <code>breadcrumbs</code>
    element to customize a single instance, or on <code>:root</code> to customize it for your entire
    app.
</p>

<CodeExample Code="@(@"<nav aria-label=""breadcrumb"">
    <ol class=""breadcrumbs"" style=""--tavenem-breadcrumb-divider:'>'"">
        <li><a href=""./"">Home</a></li>
        <li>Components</li>
        <li aria-current=""page""><a href=""./components/breadcrumbs"">Breadcrumbs</a></li>
    </ol>
</nav>")" />
